<div id="home-resources">
  <div class="head">
    <h2>About the Project</h2>
  </div>

  <div id="home-about">
    <div id="home-about-mission">
      <p id="home-about-mission-tldr">
        Open Library is an open, editable library catalog, building towards a web page for every book ever published.
        <a href="/about" class="small sansserif">More</a>
      </p>
      <p id="home-about-mission-desc">
        Just like Wikipedia, you can contribute new information or corrections to the catalog. You can browse by <a href="/subjects">subjects</a>, <a href="/authors">authors</a> or <a href="/lists">lists</a> members have created. If you love books, why not help build a library?
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-resource-section">
      <h3 class="collapse">
        <a href="https://blog.openlibrary.org/" class="header">Latest Blog Posts</a>
      </h3>
      <ul id="olBlog">
        <li><a href="https://blog.openlibrary.org/2026/04/28/security-incident-disclosure-2024-04-28/">Security Incident Disclosure</a> - <em>April 28, 2026</em></li>
        <li><a href="https://blog.openlibrary.org/2026/04/16/improving-search-by-10-percent/">Improving Search by 10%</a> - <em>April 16, 2026</em></li>
        <li><a href="https://blog.openlibrary.org/2026/04/15/canada-reads-awards/">Canada Reads Awards: My Journey Championing Canadian Content on Open Library </a> - <em>April 15, 2026</em></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

